The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Fine gesture
                                                                                                                       7                                      Fine gesture
                      
	Melbourne: A charity doubles match hastily-arranged by Roger Federer ahead of the Australian Open has so far raised more than $600,000 for the Haiti earthquake victims, officials said on Sunday.         
	The worlds top players gathered for the Hit for Haiti on the eve of the tournament a fortnight ago and it drew a crowd of around 17,000 people to Melbourne Park.         
	Gates receipts and public donations on the day raised around $ 123,000. Tennis officials said players had also donated racquets that are being auctioned on ebay and have so raised more than $38,000.         
	In addition, the ATP World Tour, Sony Ericsson WTA, ITF and the Grand Slam Committee had donated hundreds of thousands of dollars. (PTI)                                                                                                                     
